Rating: 3
I've made this a couple of times now and it has been a huge hit in my house! The skin gets crispy and tasty. I always end up having to double the amount of butter to get it all around inside the skin and also outside. Adding a bit of lemon juice to the pan is a good addition! I also cover the roasting pan with a lid for the first 2/3 of the cooking time. The first time I made them it ended up taking an hour before I figured out I should cover the pan.

Rating: 3
Delicious. The hens take a bit longer to cook through per the thermometer than the recipe indicates. I stuffed the cavity with fresh sage, a slice of the lemon after zesting, and a bit of apple. I also added crushed garlic to the butter in the skillet while browning. Liberally baste with the pan juices. Moist interior, crispy exterior, and lovely aromas.

Rating: 4
Instead of the Sage Butter, I used some whiskey butter that I had made for steak the other day (whiskey/burbon/shallots/garlic/dijon/s&p) It tasted great! Lemon wedge in the hole made for a good contrast

