We made this for tksgiving and the guys loved it. Took advice of the reviewers for lemon inside with fresh sage and abit more zest in the butter. Will use this recipe many times.

Rating: 4
I needed something simple to do for a small thanksgiving dinner, and this fit the bill perfectly. The hens were fantastic, tho I think I need to practice separating the skin from the meat to rub on the butter. Upped the lemon zest a little, and took the advice of a previous cook and put a wedge of lemon in each bird. I look forward to making this again.

Rating: 3
this dish was delicious and very easy to make. i added more lemon zest and proscuitto to the butter rub mixture and it turned out great.

Rating: 3
Easy, quick, and looks impressive on the table. Made for a wonderfully romantic dinner. I made this for the first time this weekend and paired it with steamed asparagus and baked potato as sides. I used fresh sage and doubled the lemon zest. I also stuffed each hen with a slice of lemon, which infused the meat with a lovely fresh flavor, but was not overpowering. I did brown them in the skillet. I was surprised at how effortless this step was, and it made for a nice presentation. I'll definitely make this again.

Rating: 2
I loved the sage & butter rubdown for the bird, but didn't like the cornish hen much. I think next time, I'll use a whole fryer instead. That way, I'll get more than one plate of food. I must agree with the other reviewers, the lemon zest adds a bit of zippiness to the dish. This would go over well with either chicken (as previously stated) or with turkey for thxsgiving.

